OL,3,CTalks to resume as Irish fuel protests
OL,4,Center fifth day
OL,6,FThe Irish Government is to re-enter
OL,7,Ftalks on Saturday aimed at defusing
OL,8,Fprotests which have strangled the
OL,9,Fdistribution of fuel around the
OL,10,Fcountry.
OL,12,FA series of protests, which have
OL,13,Finvolved blockades at key fuel
OL,14,Fdistribution sites, are continuing for
OL,15,Fa fifth consecutive day after a crunch
OL,16,Fmeeting on Friday failed to end with
OL,17,Fconcrete proposals.
OL,19,FProtesters say the Government needs to
OL,20,Ftake urgent action on fuel prices or
OL,21,Fthey will go out of business.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
