PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775952175
OL,3,CTalks to resume as Irish fuel protests
OL,4,Center fifth day
OL,6,FThere were fears that around a third
OL,7,Fof Ireland's 1,500 filling stations
OL,8,Fwould have run dry by morning as
OL,9,Fprotesters engaged in a blockade of
OL,10,Fthe country's only oil refinery in
OL,11,FWhitegate, Co Cork, as well as key
OL,12,Fdepots in Galway and Foynes, Co
OL,13,FLimerick.
OL,15,FThere have also been concerns about
OL,16,Ffuel shortages leading to curtailments
OL,17,Fon the provision of emergency services
OL,18,Fand the delivery of vital goods `
OL,19,Fwhile the National Emergency
OL,20,FCoordination Group urged the public to
OL,21,Fonly buy the fuel they need.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
